I cannot fetch, pull or push since having installed the latest update 2.6.6.0 because whenever I do I get the error

 
{code:java}
C:/Users /Thomas: line1: syntax error near unexpected token `('{code}
 

I was able to narrow down the search for the cause and found out that it is *due to a whitespace character in my Windows user name*, e.g. the location of the credential manager is

 
{code:java}
C:/Users/Thomas Flinkow/AppData/Local/Atlassian/SourceTree/git_extras/git-credential-manager.exe{code}
 

and it seems to not work because of the whitespace character between "Thomas" and "Flinkow".

When I move the git-credential-manager.exe to a path that does not contain a whitespace character, everything works fine.

But I don't want to have to rely on an inconvenient workaround; instead of having to copy & paste every git command to the console, edit the path by hand and execute it then every time I want to fetch, push or pull I want to be able to simply press the buttons in the UI like it was possible before the update.

Sometimes I just want to see if changes in a previous commit affect a current issue without generating a new commit.

On the command line I can issue the command
{code:java}
git revert --no-commit a1b2c3d4{code}
I would like to be able to do the same thing using Sourcetree.

The git hook pre_push doesn't seem to work.

 

Steps to reproduce (simple test):

Create a simple file "pre_push" in ".git/hooks" like this:
{code:java}
#!/bin/sh
echo hello > pre_push.log.txt
{code}
Make sure it's encoding is utf-8 and the line endings are linux style.

Confirm that it's working by opening the git bash and run ".git/hooks/pre_push". The file "pre_push.log.txt" should be created. Remove it for the real test.

Now push something to another repo using SourceTree. The file will not be created

Config file:
{code:java}
[diff "cp932"]
    textconv = iconv -f cp932 -t utf-8


{code}
Gitatttibutes file:
{code:java}
*.vb diff=cp932
*.sql diff=cp932{code}
It works for uncommitted files. I can see multi-bytes texts on the diff window of SourceTree.

But it doesn't work with committed or unstaged files. I see a lot of the question symbol in a black diamond(mojibake).

As a trial, I changed the textconv setting to 'noconv' instead of 'iconv'. Of cource there is no noconv.exe in my computer, So checking diff for uncommitted has stopped working. But checking diff for committed or unstaged files are still working with mojibake.

When we want for instance to access a remote repository, we add an account that points towards our Bitbucket server instance.

If login/password are wrong, we have the normal error :

Authentication failed.

If login/password are rights, we have this new error :

" Sourcetree was unable to find a password for user xxx at xxx."

In atlassian-bitbucket-access.log, we have a 200 OK access to :
